brella of enterprising action.This innovative approach will be of great interest to scholars in entrepreneurship, social entrepreneurship, cultural entrepreneurship, cultural studies, and consumer culture, as well as for policy makers in public and local government, regional development and cultural event management"--cProvided by publisher.  a43 0aEntrepreneurshipxSocial aspects. 0aNew business enterprises. 0aConsumer behavior.1 aTimm Knudsen, Britta,eeditor.1 aChristensen, Dorthe Refslund,eeditor.1 aBlenker, Per,eeditor. 0aRoutledge studies in entrepreneurship ;v5.  aHB 615 E5956 2015c1hUAHS-Bi0162035173234  aHB 615 E5956 2015wLCc1i0162035173234lON_SHELFmUAHSSp$150.00rYsYtBOOKu10/22/201401ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2014015888bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/307431148